Jesse&#x27;s &quot;stir DOM&quot; fuzzer, which fits in a tweet & a bookmarklet:<p><pre><code>    pick = a => a[a.length * Math.random() | 0];
    elts = document.all;
    stir = () => pick(elts).appendChild(pick(elts));
    setInterval(stir, 1);
</code></pre>
